03:02.760 --> 03:05.562
I need to come up with
a less shameless version

03:05.596 --> 03:07.464
of "Dear Buckner parent I don't know."

03:08.716 --> 03:11.718
And then there's this project manager guy.

03:11.752 --> 03:13.520
I met him when I was dumpster diving

03:13.554 --> 03:15.388
at this building he was renovating.

03:15.423 --> 03:16.639
Was that in a Sandra Bullock movie?

03:16.691 --> 03:19.392
Yeah, I know.

03:19.427 --> 03:22.796
Just trying to work every
angle I can think of.

03:22.830 --> 03:24.698
I'm not really sure
that I can pull this off.

03:24.732 --> 03:26.649
Is there anything I can do?

03:26.701 --> 03:28.401
Not unless you've got an extra 50 grand

03:28.436 --> 03:29.536
to remodel your bedroom?

03:31.438 --> 03:32.672
You have practice this early?

03:32.707 --> 03:34.607
No, I lost a bet.

03:34.625 --> 03:38.444
So I have to pick up
this girl in Kendall Park.

03:38.462 --> 03:39.612
Wait wait wait wait wait.

03:39.630 --> 03:42.382
Is everything else
okay? School, the clinic?

03:42.416 --> 03:44.484
All good.

03:44.518 --> 03:47.520
Maybe I should rename the business "R&D."

03:47.555 --> 03:49.823
At least our initials can be together.

04:04.405 --> 04:05.655
Hi.

04:05.689 --> 04:07.640
Our first game's tomorrow.

04:07.658 --> 04:08.775
Will you be there?

04:08.809 --> 04:10.677
Will you?

04:10.711 --> 04:12.679
Don't you have community
service at the clinic?

04:14.482 --> 04:16.783
I worked my schedule around the game.

04:16.817 --> 04:19.486
Ah.

04:19.519 --> 04:21.454
Count me in.

04:24.425 --> 04:26.342
Hey.

04:28.345 --> 04:29.796
So you ready?

04:29.830 --> 04:32.365
I'd better be. John's gonna be there.

04:32.399 --> 04:33.533
What?

04:33.567 --> 04:36.536
He's coming to our first game?

04:36.570 --> 04:39.706
I just thought we'd have
a few games under our belt

04:39.740 --> 04:42.442
before he showed up and told me everything

04:42.476 --> 04:43.676
I'm doing wrong.

04:43.694 --> 04:44.727
You're not doing anything wrong.

04:44.779 --> 04:46.613
The team's gonna be fine.

04:46.647 --> 04:48.615
Huh? If I can just get you and Sharee

04:48.649 --> 04:51.618
to work together, then
we might have a chance.

04:53.521 --> 04:55.555
I can do that.

04:56.590 --> 04:58.524
Thanks.

05:01.745 --> 05:03.329
Honey.

05:03.363 --> 05:04.664
You want some raspberry for your cereal?

05:04.698 --> 05:06.549
What? No.

05:06.584 --> 05:07.750
No, wait. Oh, I don't know.

05:09.386 --> 05:11.370
It's awfully early in the school year

05:11.388 --> 05:14.340
for you to be so stressed out.

05:14.374 --> 05:17.663
I'm trying to figure out all my
stuff for early admission into Pratt,

05:17.678 --> 05:19.679
and there's just, like a lot...

05:19.713 --> 05:21.481
Well, you know what Grandpa Bill would say.

05:21.515 --> 05:22.782
"You gotta diversify."

05:22.817 --> 05:25.318
Prove to them that you're
not the totally average person

05:25.352 --> 05:26.486
"that I know you are."

05:26.520 --> 05:28.555
You're not average, and neither is Bay.

05:28.589 --> 05:29.789
Compared to the thousands of kids

05:29.824 --> 05:31.791
applying for like 40 spots,

05:31.826 --> 05:33.459
I might be.

05:33.494 --> 05:34.761
I just hope a recommendation letter

05:34.795 --> 05:36.796
from Teresa Ledarsky will mean something.

05:36.831 --> 05:38.598
Teresa who?

05:38.632 --> 05:40.433
My art teacher.

05:40.467 --> 05:41.801
She was a very important figure

05:41.836 --> 05:43.670
in the '80s performance art scene.

05:43.704 --> 05:44.754
Performance art?

05:44.788 --> 05:46.405
Yeah.

05:46.423 --> 05:47.540
You may not be that
impressed with her work,

05:47.575 --> 05:48.741
but Pratt will be.

05:48.776 --> 05:50.376
I just hope that she's impressed with me.

05:51.645 --> 05:53.780
Okay. Go get 'em, tiger.

05:53.814 --> 05:55.348
See you at practice.

05:59.520 --> 06:02.272
Oh, honey, I have some leftover tuna salad

06:02.306 --> 06:03.556
for lunch if you want it.

06:03.590 --> 06:04.724
Ah, that's okay.

06:04.758 --> 06:06.593
I actually wanted to talk
to you about something.

06:06.627 --> 06:08.428
I hope you don't freak out

06:08.462 --> 06:10.396
or burst into tears.

06:10.431 --> 06:12.398
What?

06:12.433 --> 06:14.701
I'm thinking about getting my own place.

06:16.370 --> 06:18.371
I talked to dad already,
and he's cool with it.

06:18.405 --> 06:20.373
You talked to dad?

06:20.407 --> 06:21.708
Well, I didn't want to leave you out.

06:21.742 --> 06:23.543
I just told him I wanted to talk about it

06:23.577 --> 06:25.712
with you myself.

06:25.746 --> 06:29.449
Well, I'm excited for you.

06:29.483 --> 06:31.351
You are?

06:31.385 --> 06:34.387
Of course. It's your first place.

06:34.421 --> 06:35.555
Have you found anything yet?

06:35.589 --> 06:37.457
Do you need help?

06:37.491 --> 06:39.459
Well, there was this one place

06:39.493 --> 06:40.793
that we looked at before the wedding,

06:40.828 --> 06:42.428
but it's gone.

06:42.463 --> 06:44.631
I'm checking out a few later on today.

06:44.665 --> 06:46.532
You know what, Renzo has a friend

06:46.567 --> 06:47.700
that's a rental agent.

06:47.735 --> 06:49.636
I'll call him and see if he can help out.

06:49.670 --> 06:51.638
Great.

06:51.672 --> 06:54.473
Thanks!

07:17.431 --> 07:18.681
Morning! Sorry I'm late.

07:18.716 --> 07:20.333
White girl on this side of town...

07:20.367 --> 07:22.735
thought maybe you got carjacked.

07:26.506 --> 07:28.674
I drove through Norm's.

07:28.692 --> 07:30.677
Got your breakfast burrito.

07:30.711 --> 07:32.528
Thanks.

07:32.563 --> 07:35.348
So Toby and I were talking
about field hockey this morning,

07:35.366 --> 07:37.750
and let's face it...

07:37.785 --> 07:40.320
you and I are going to
be carrying this team.

07:40.354 --> 07:42.522
So if you ever wanted to
go over the playbook and...

07:42.556 --> 07:44.590
Why aren't we moving?

07:44.625 --> 07:46.392
The whole deaf thing.

07:46.427 --> 07:48.561
I can't really talk and
drive at the same time.

07:48.595 --> 07:51.764
Unless you're up for a
really scary ride to school.

07:51.799 --> 07:55.435
Wasn't planning on talking.

07:55.469 --> 07:56.753
Okay.

08:02.726 --> 08:04.543
In and out of the cones. In and out.

08:04.561 --> 08:05.711
Stay low, stay low.

08:05.729 --> 08:07.430
Nice job, nice job.

08:07.481 --> 08:10.316
Eyes up! Eyes up! Eyes up.

08:10.351 --> 08:11.601
All right, Bay. Here we go.

08:11.652 --> 08:13.486
Side to side. Side to side.

08:13.520 --> 08:14.570
Right hand a little lower.

08:14.605 --> 08:16.606
- Oh, okay.
- You got it.

08:18.609 --> 08:20.610
Good job, Bay. Keep it up.

08:23.664 --> 08:25.564
Hey! Watch it.

08:28.452 --> 08:30.670
That's it. Good job.

08:38.578 --> 08:40.578
So how's it going with Sharee?

08:40.597 --> 08:43.599
I tried to talk with her about some plays,

08:43.634 --> 08:46.419
but she totally shut me down.

08:53.560 --> 08:56.312
I'd say stick with the not-talking thing.

08:56.363 --> 08:57.613
Yeah.

08:57.648 --> 09:00.616
Nice shot.

09:00.651 --> 09:02.435
So where'd you learn that?

09:02.453 --> 09:04.603
It's called YouTube.

09:04.621 --> 09:06.572
Okay...

09:06.606 --> 09:09.325
Let's see what you two can
do with some give and gos.

09:09.376 --> 09:10.609
- Sure.
- Let's keep going, guys.

09:10.627 --> 09:12.378
Here we go, here we go, here we go.

09:12.413 --> 09:15.381
Hey, Bay. Come on.

09:35.602 --> 09:39.472
See? This is why you have me on the bench.

09:41.492 --> 09:44.310
Yeah! You two are like
Lebron and Wade out there.

09:44.328 --> 09:46.696
Yeah, I'm Lebron. She's Wade.

09:51.685 --> 09:53.653
Yes, it's a toilet.

09:53.687 --> 09:55.671
But it's also a question.

09:55.706 --> 09:57.623
Duchamp is playing with the whole idea

09:57.658 --> 09:59.392
of art as a commodity.

09:59.426 --> 10:02.495
As something that you can buy
to show status and privilege.

10:02.529 --> 10:03.763
It's also hilarious.

10:03.797 --> 10:05.531
Exactly.

10:05.566 --> 10:08.568
That's why we're still talking
about it 100 years later.

10:10.404 --> 10:12.405
Okay, we'll pick this up on Thursday.

10:12.439 --> 10:13.606
Remember, no class tomorrow,

10:13.640 --> 10:15.641
and get those paper proposals in.

10:21.698 --> 10:23.349
Well, great.

10:23.367 --> 10:24.617
Now I'm just supposed
to tell the difference

10:24.651 --> 10:27.403
between smart dumbass and just dumbass.

10:27.454 --> 10:28.538
Why are you still carrying that thing?

10:28.572 --> 10:29.622
I thought you pledged already.

10:29.656 --> 10:31.657
Yeah, I got caught without the brick again.

10:31.691 --> 10:32.825
Kind of getting used to it, though.

10:32.859 --> 10:34.693
You heading out?

10:34.711 --> 10:36.546
Uh, hang on.

10:36.580 --> 10:38.714
Okay.

10:38.749 --> 10:40.533
Professor Ledarsky.

10:40.551 --> 10:42.418
Teresa.

10:42.469 --> 10:43.753
I was wondering if you would be willing

10:43.804 --> 10:45.605
to help me out with my
application to Pratt.

10:45.639 --> 10:47.740
I really need a letter of recommendation.

10:47.774 --> 10:49.392
And I know we just got started,

10:49.426 --> 10:50.576
but it would be so amazing

10:50.611 --> 10:51.711
if you would consider writing me one.

10:51.745 --> 10:54.597
Um, I really don't have much to go on.

10:54.648 --> 10:56.582
I know, which is why

10:56.617 --> 10:59.519
maybe I could help you out at your studio.

10:59.553 --> 11:01.454
You could look at some of my work.

11:01.488 --> 11:03.556
Well, actually,

11:03.590 --> 11:05.691
I'm in a show in Minneapolis tomorrow.

11:05.725 --> 11:08.594
If you wouldn't mind
helping loading a 200-pound

11:08.629 --> 11:11.364
bronze sculpture into an old station wagon,

11:11.398 --> 11:13.332
driving six hours,

11:13.367 --> 11:15.468
eating some cheese, looking at some art,

11:15.502 --> 11:16.736
I wouldn't mind the help.

11:16.770 --> 11:18.671
That sounds perfect.

11:18.705 --> 11:23.509
We may need some help
with the loading part.

11:25.462 --> 11:26.596
Tank.

11:26.630 --> 11:29.682
How would you like to road-trip
with me to Minneapolis,

11:29.716 --> 11:32.585
earn major brownie points from Teresa,

11:32.619 --> 11:34.453
look at some funky art, and
eat really bad road food?

11:34.488 --> 11:35.788
Uh, dude...

11:35.822 --> 11:37.723
you had me at "road trip."

