13:12.936 --> 13:14.437
I can't get over how
incredible that place was.

13:14.471 --> 13:16.472
It's like living in New York.

13:16.490 --> 13:17.657
Mom, you've never lived in New York.

13:17.691 --> 13:20.476
That little corner store...
you could just run over there

13:20.494 --> 13:21.644
if you need some milk.

13:21.662 --> 13:23.446
It's a super-convenient convenience store.

13:23.480 --> 13:25.882
Well, actually, I could just bring some by.

13:25.916 --> 13:28.834
It's that close.

13:28.869 --> 13:30.703
You could even do your laundry here.

13:30.754 --> 13:32.889
Oh, and I know that your dad

13:32.923 --> 13:35.875
is gonna love that grill in the backyard.

13:35.926 --> 13:37.660
I just...

13:37.694 --> 13:38.895
I don't know if I can afford it.

13:38.929 --> 13:40.863
I read somewhere that
rent's not supposed to be

13:40.898 --> 13:42.765
more than 1/3 of your monthly income.

13:42.799 --> 13:45.551
Oh! We could help you.

13:45.602 --> 13:47.637
- Really?
- Yeah, we were going to have to pay

13:47.671 --> 13:49.805
for your housing in college anyway, so...

13:49.839 --> 13:51.908
I guess.

13:51.942 --> 13:53.693
Hey!

13:53.727 --> 13:55.645
So great news.

13:55.679 --> 13:57.897
Remember that letter of recommendation

13:57.948 --> 13:59.732
I needed from my art teacher?

13:59.783 --> 14:01.884
She is having an art show
tomorrow in Minneapolis

14:01.919 --> 14:04.453
and she invited me to help her out.

14:04.488 --> 14:05.755
It would be a great opportunity

14:05.789 --> 14:07.690
for me to be exposed to the art world

14:07.724 --> 14:10.693
with a real artist, and all I
need from you is permission to go.

14:10.792 --> 14:12.593
Well, okay. I guess.

14:12.628 --> 14:15.596
Actually, you also need
permission from your coach.

14:15.631 --> 14:17.865
Because you have a game tomorrow.

14:17.899 --> 14:19.667
Everyone else has a game.

14:19.701 --> 14:21.502
I have a date with a bench.

14:21.536 --> 14:23.704
You have an obligation to your team.

14:23.814 --> 14:25.748
Why don't you just play the game

14:25.782 --> 14:27.616
- and then go?
- The show's in the afternoon.

14:27.651 --> 14:29.752
I'd miss the whole thing.

14:29.786 --> 14:30.953
I need my players on the field.

14:30.987 --> 14:33.572
You have a choice to make.

14:33.623 --> 14:36.692
Between art and field hockey...

14:36.727 --> 14:38.661
what do you think I'm going to pick?

14:38.695 --> 14:40.746
Fine. You're off the team.

14:43.633 --> 14:45.601
Am I supposed to be upset?

14:46.703 --> 14:49.054
Then I ran a wire through the faucet

14:49.089 --> 14:51.006
and put a switch on the spigot,

14:51.040 --> 14:52.057
and there you go.

14:52.092 --> 14:54.643
The fruits of your dumpster.

14:54.678 --> 14:56.679
Interesting.

14:56.713 --> 14:58.564
I have to admit... I didn't come here

14:58.598 --> 14:59.715
just to show you a lamp.

14:59.733 --> 15:01.650
When I'm not digging through dumpsters,

15:01.685 --> 15:03.786
I also run K&D design.

15:03.820 --> 15:05.571
We're a small firm, but we've done a lot

15:05.605 --> 15:06.822
of different work spaces.

15:06.857 --> 15:09.692
I definitely think we can
help you with this one.

15:09.726 --> 15:11.894
Yeah, I could use some
help with my furniture.

15:11.928 --> 15:13.863
Maybe you just need the right designer.

15:13.897 --> 15:17.867
I took the liberty of
bringing our look-book.

15:17.901 --> 15:21.704
This was a raw space when we started.

15:21.738 --> 15:22.922
We kept the openness.

15:22.956 --> 15:24.907
And this was a print shop

15:24.925 --> 15:26.041
that just needed a quick makeover.

15:26.075 --> 15:29.011
Yeah. I like your lamp.

15:29.045 --> 15:31.931
The whole idea of
repurposing discarded stuff.

15:31.965 --> 15:33.883
- That's good.
- Yeah.

15:33.917 --> 15:36.635
- Are you free tomorrow?
- I... I can be.

15:36.686 --> 15:38.587
- Hey, Jess!
- Yeah.

15:38.622 --> 15:40.055
Can we get another one on
the flight to Denver tomorrow?

15:40.089 --> 15:41.657
We're flying?

15:41.691 --> 15:42.825
Is that a problem?

15:42.859 --> 15:44.593
Oh! No, I just...

15:44.628 --> 15:46.061
so last minute, I didn't
want to put you out.

15:46.096 --> 15:47.730
Oh, you're not putting anyone out.

15:47.764 --> 15:48.898
It's my jet.

15:48.932 --> 15:50.866
You don't have a desk,

15:50.901 --> 15:51.967
but you have a jet.

15:52.002 --> 15:53.736
Yeah.

15:53.770 --> 15:55.788
Huh. Okay.

15:55.822 --> 15:58.741
Hey, did you see the
Jayhawks play Iowa last night?

15:58.775 --> 16:00.659
Mm-hmm. What's the sign for Jayhawks?

16:00.710 --> 16:02.578
- Jayhawks.
- Jayhawks.

16:02.612 --> 16:03.946
Man, that's cool. I needed to know that one

16:03.964 --> 16:05.748
'cause this year we're going all the way.

16:05.782 --> 16:06.882
Mm-hmm.

16:06.917 --> 16:08.634
What are you doing after school?

16:08.668 --> 16:09.785
Gotta get to my job. Why?

16:09.803 --> 16:11.003
Just wondering if you wanted

16:11.054 --> 16:12.721
to squeeze in one more practice.

16:12.756 --> 16:14.623
Why are you so worried about this game?

16:14.641 --> 16:15.724
It's not like it's the playoffs.

16:15.759 --> 16:17.626
Not that we'll ever get that far.

16:17.644 --> 16:19.929
Uh, my dad's gonna be there.

16:19.963 --> 16:21.764
And I just kind of wanted us to do good.

16:21.798 --> 16:23.732
Mm, just keep getting the ball to me,

16:23.767 --> 16:24.850
and we'll be fine.

16:30.941 --> 16:31.991
What's your name?

16:32.025 --> 16:34.910
Sharee Gifford, why?

16:34.945 --> 16:36.679
Stand over there.

16:36.713 --> 16:38.030
What'd we do?

16:38.081 --> 16:40.783
Use the wrong water fountain?

16:40.817 --> 16:42.952
- Locker search.
- You can't do that.

16:42.986 --> 16:45.020
Yeah, we can. It's school property.

16:57.339 --> 16:58.613
____

17:00.411 --> 17:04.066
____

17:04.067 --> 17:07.284
____

17:07.285 --> 17:11.107
____

17:11.108 --> 17:12.767
____

17:16.160 --> 17:18.559
____

17:19.220 --> 17:21.512
____

17:34.804 --> 17:36.005
Oh, hey!

17:36.039 --> 17:38.607
Someone put Hoffman's
first scrimmage online.

17:38.642 --> 17:40.876
We should totally put Sharee
on their left defender.

17:40.911 --> 17:43.012
I just got off the phone
with principal rose.

17:43.046 --> 17:46.882
Sharee is not going to be
playing in the game tomorrow.

17:46.917 --> 17:47.917
Why not?

17:49.819 --> 17:52.571
They found a knife in her locker.

17:53.857 --> 17:56.625
So she got expelled.

18:11.067 --> 18:12.201
What are you doing here?

18:12.235 --> 18:15.020
Toby told me you got expelled from school.

18:15.038 --> 18:16.956
Yeah. On the bright side,

18:16.990 --> 18:18.157
you don't have to pick me up anymore.

18:18.191 --> 18:19.892
How can you make a joke about this?

18:19.926 --> 18:21.093
What am I supposed to do?

18:21.127 --> 18:23.229
The principal said I'm lucky
she didn't call the cops.

18:23.263 --> 18:26.131
- Why did you have a knife?
- It was a box cutter.

18:26.166 --> 18:27.833
A what?

18:27.867 --> 18:29.034
I told you I work after school.

18:29.069 --> 18:32.238
I cut open boxes at a grocery store.

18:32.272 --> 18:34.073
I must have left it in my bag.

18:34.107 --> 18:36.308
Why didn't the metal detectors catch it?

18:36.343 --> 18:37.910
I don't know.

18:37.944 --> 18:39.878
Well, did you tell
Principal Rose all of this?

18:39.896 --> 18:41.247
She didn't believe me.
All she wanted to know

18:41.281 --> 18:42.881
is why do I hate deaf kids?

18:42.916 --> 18:44.049
I told her she's crazy.

18:44.117 --> 18:45.884
I didn't slash those tires.

18:45.919 --> 18:47.086
I didn't break any windows.

18:50.890 --> 18:53.192
Wait, those windows were
smashed before school.

18:53.226 --> 18:54.927
Yeah, so?

18:54.961 --> 18:56.161
I picked you up.

18:56.196 --> 18:58.998
We went to practice and then
Ms. Troyer's class together.

18:59.032 --> 19:01.800
It couldn't have been
you. We're fighting this.

19:01.835 --> 19:03.118
I'm not going back to that racist school.

19:03.169 --> 19:06.171
Stop! Carlton is a good school.

19:06.206 --> 19:07.873
They just made a mistake.

19:07.907 --> 19:09.124
Come in with me tomorrow,

19:09.175 --> 19:11.010
and we'll talk to Principal Rose together.

19:26.026 --> 19:28.994
She can't show up, but she's
happy to take her commission.

19:29.064 --> 19:30.097
Is that your dealer?

19:30.131 --> 19:31.148
My agent.

19:31.182 --> 19:33.300
Hey, this trip will involve pizza

19:33.318 --> 19:34.902
at some point, right?

19:34.936 --> 19:36.854
Yeah, you guys call the food stops.

19:36.905 --> 19:40.040
I'm choosing the music, 'cause
the crap you kids listen to...

19:40.075 --> 19:42.109
I know. I can't stand most of it either.

19:42.143 --> 19:43.310
I mean, what's up with that?

19:43.328 --> 19:44.978
I can't even hear a band.

19:44.996 --> 19:47.081
It sounds like everything
has been done on a laptop.

19:47.115 --> 19:48.248
Well, I like some old-school stuff.

19:48.283 --> 19:50.150
A little Bob Marley.

19:50.168 --> 19:51.919
Of course you do.

19:51.953 --> 19:53.320
You heard of Patti Smith?

19:53.338 --> 19:55.122
Yeah.

19:55.156 --> 19:56.340
A little.

19:58.176 --> 20:00.878
I saw her at CBGB's.

20:00.929 --> 20:03.163
Changed my life.

20:03.181 --> 20:05.215
This chick out of Jersey.

20:05.266 --> 20:07.334
She didn't give a damn what anybody thinks

20:07.352 --> 20:10.354
of the way she dresses
or the way she sounds.

20:10.388 --> 20:12.072
You know what...

20:12.107 --> 20:14.174
you're at your best when
you don't give a crap.

20:14.209 --> 20:16.944
Here, put this on.

20:30.962 --> 20:32.096
Sorry I'm late.

20:32.130 --> 20:33.263
You've got copies of your pay stubs, right?

20:33.298 --> 20:34.998
Yeah, mom...

20:35.016 --> 20:36.183
We've gotta get going.

20:36.217 --> 20:38.102
I told the leasing office
we'd be there by 2:00.

20:38.136 --> 20:41.004
Yeah, I already called to cancel.

20:41.039 --> 20:42.222
Why? We can still make it.

20:42.273 --> 20:45.142
I found another place.

20:45.176 --> 20:47.044
It's in Edgewater.

20:47.078 --> 20:49.246
It's a one-bedroom. It's
got a washer and dryer.

20:49.280 --> 20:51.148
Edgewater is 30 minutes away,

20:51.182 --> 20:52.950
and it's not a very
good neighborhood, honey.

20:52.984 --> 20:54.118
It's
up-and-coming,

20:54.152 --> 20:56.286
and I can afford it on my own.

20:56.321 --> 20:58.188
I told you that we would help you.

20:58.223 --> 21:00.224
I signed the lease papers this morning.

21:01.960 --> 21:03.093
Oh.

21:03.128 --> 21:05.996
I think you're really going to like it.

21:06.030 --> 21:07.881
You know? It's charming.

21:07.916 --> 21:10.134
The molding, it's original.

21:10.168 --> 21:11.969
You got married without us.

21:12.003 --> 21:13.237
You found a new place without us.

21:13.271 --> 21:15.172
I got married without you

21:15.206 --> 21:17.274
because you weren't
supportive of my relationship.

21:17.308 --> 21:19.343
You keep making all these big decisions

21:19.377 --> 21:20.878
without talking to us first.

21:20.912 --> 21:22.246
Mom, I'm married and I still live

21:22.280 --> 21:24.281
at home with my parents.

21:24.315 --> 21:26.950
Nikki and I are going to
need a place of our own

21:26.985 --> 21:28.886
and I want to be able to pay for it.

21:28.920 --> 21:30.921
I'm just trying to man up here.

21:30.955 --> 21:33.941
I'm going to talk to your dad about this.

21:41.199 --> 21:44.168
Wow, this place is amazing.

21:44.202 --> 21:46.370
Yeah, Minneapolis. Who knew?

21:46.404 --> 21:48.238
You must be Teresa. I'm Eve.

21:48.256 --> 21:50.040
- We emailed.
- Yes, hi.

21:50.074 --> 21:51.341
It's such an honor to have you here.

21:51.376 --> 21:54.044
I don't think I mentionned, but
I wrote part of my thesis on you.

21:54.078 --> 21:55.979
And I'm not even dead yet.

21:56.014 --> 21:57.848
Those are my assistants.

21:57.882 --> 21:58.849
Bay and Tank.

21:58.883 --> 21:59.933
Hey.

21:59.968 --> 22:01.118
This place is so cool.

22:01.152 --> 22:02.920
Thanks.

22:02.954 --> 22:04.888
She's the artist. I'm just the muscle.

22:04.923 --> 22:06.857
Speaking of which,

22:06.891 --> 22:08.926
where should we put this bad boy?

22:17.101 --> 22:18.318
Oh...

22:18.369 --> 22:21.071
Uh, unfortunately we're
keeping the floor open

22:21.105 --> 22:23.106
for some performances.

22:23.141 --> 22:24.875
Was this in the images you submitted?

22:24.909 --> 22:26.877
I brought new work.

22:26.911 --> 22:30.047
Okay, well, there is this wall here.

22:31.916 --> 22:33.250
Oh, got it. Okay.

22:33.284 --> 22:36.303
I'll make some selections.

22:36.337 --> 22:38.989
Well, let me know if you
need any help hanging.

22:39.023 --> 22:40.257
We're so excited.

22:40.291 --> 22:41.892
It's really nice to meet you.

22:41.926 --> 22:43.026
You too.

22:44.262 --> 22:45.896
I have a feeling we're going to be

22:45.930 --> 22:48.015
subjected to a DJ at some point.

22:50.018 --> 22:51.902
Well, this stuff is so great.

22:51.936 --> 22:53.187
Well, hang the new pieces

22:53.238 --> 22:55.989
and I'll take the old stuff away.

23:01.029 --> 23:03.914
Okay, this thing is going
to give me nightmares.

23:03.948 --> 23:06.200
It looks a little gargoyle-ish.

23:06.251 --> 23:09.152
It looks like something my
stoner cousin made at Ren Faire.

23:09.170 --> 23:10.337
You can't be into this.

23:10.339 --> 23:13.023
You know what, I am not
here to be an art critic.

23:13.057 --> 23:14.925
I am here to get you a
letter of recommendation.

23:14.959 --> 23:15.926
Roger that.

23:18.263 --> 23:19.863
I'm still trying to convince them

23:19.898 --> 23:21.164
to do a cafe off the main lobby here.

23:21.199 --> 23:24.134
I can't believe the city
was going to tear this down.

23:24.168 --> 23:25.852
People never know what they have.

23:25.887 --> 23:28.338
I saw that old movie
theater you did in Austin.

23:28.356 --> 23:30.891
This is even more beautiful.

23:30.942 --> 23:32.059
So you finally looked me up, huh?

23:32.110 --> 23:33.894
Believe me, it's a good thing

23:33.945 --> 23:36.313
that I didn't know who you were
before I showed you that lamp.

23:36.347 --> 23:39.199
Hey... why don't you work with me on this?

23:39.234 --> 23:40.918
Me?

23:40.952 --> 23:43.120
Well, your firm. Do the interiors.

23:43.154 --> 23:45.022
I'm not... I mean,

23:45.056 --> 23:47.291
yes, I would love to.

23:47.325 --> 23:49.960
But I've never done restoration.

23:49.994 --> 23:51.161
No no no. I want to start new in there.

23:51.195 --> 23:53.046
Do something like your lamp.

23:53.081 --> 23:55.916
Use salvaged parts, but completely turn

23:55.967 --> 23:57.033
the whole thing on its head.

23:57.051 --> 23:59.303
Something fun and playful.

23:59.337 --> 24:02.256
- Smart.
- That would be incredible.

24:02.307 --> 24:03.974
- Yes!
- Great.

24:04.008 --> 24:06.143
How soon can you be here?

24:06.177 --> 24:08.228
We wouldn't work from K.C.?

24:08.263 --> 24:11.214
I would need you on site, but
it wouldn't be for very long.

24:11.249 --> 24:13.016
Four months, six tops.

24:13.051 --> 24:15.018
Oh.

24:15.052 --> 24:16.920
This is really hard to say,

24:16.955 --> 24:20.157
but both my daughters are in
their senior year of high school,

24:20.191 --> 24:22.092
and I really need to be home.

24:22.126 --> 24:24.227
You're kidding me, right?

24:24.262 --> 24:26.113
Well, they're getting
ready to go off to college.

24:26.164 --> 24:27.264
It's a really big year.

24:27.298 --> 24:29.116
What, they need you to pack their lunch?

24:29.167 --> 24:31.935
- They're 17.
- Can I come on the weekends?

24:31.970 --> 24:33.270
When the crew's not here.

24:33.304 --> 24:35.138
Or we could wait till June.

24:35.173 --> 24:36.906
You want me to stall my
project for nine months...

24:36.924 --> 24:38.875
just send everyone home for a year.

24:38.910 --> 24:42.245
Then I guess I have to say no.

24:42.263 --> 24:44.931
And I'm really sorry. And thank you.

24:44.966 --> 24:46.967
You know what, this is unbelievable.

24:47.018 --> 24:48.251
You have an opportunity

24:48.269 --> 24:50.354
to completely change the scale
of your dinky little firm.

24:50.388 --> 24:53.290
What is it? You like doing
two-bit kitchen makeovers?

24:53.324 --> 24:55.892
Or Laura Ashley funeral parlors?

24:55.926 --> 24:58.094
You know what, forget it. Offer rescinded.

25:02.181 --> 25:03.214
Sounds nice.

25:03.232 --> 25:04.432
Says there's plenty of street parking.

25:04.483 --> 25:05.566
It's close to Carlton.

25:05.781 --> 25:07.365
I drove by and the house next door

25:07.399 --> 25:08.732
looks like something out of a horror movie.

25:09.650 --> 25:12.185
If there's traffic, it's going to take him

25:12.236 --> 25:13.653
45 minutes to get back here.

25:13.688 --> 25:15.439
So you're okay with him moving out

25:15.473 --> 25:17.240
as long as it's in throwing distance?

25:17.275 --> 25:18.608
I just don't think he should be moving

25:18.642 --> 25:21.278
all the way across town to a
neighborhood that is not safe.

25:21.312 --> 25:23.663
He is a married man, and
I for one am quite proud

25:23.698 --> 25:25.515
that he wants to pay his own rent.

25:25.550 --> 25:26.649
Oh, so I'm an enabler.

25:26.667 --> 25:28.251
I didn't say that.

25:28.286 --> 25:30.587
I really think you should
back me up on this, John.

25:30.621 --> 25:33.423
Kathryn.

25:33.458 --> 25:35.625
The last time you went to visit your mom,

25:35.660 --> 25:38.361
you paid $250

25:38.396 --> 25:40.464
so you could leave 10 hours early

25:40.498 --> 25:42.566
because she is still telling you

25:42.600 --> 25:44.234
how to live your life.

25:46.704 --> 25:48.672
Don't be that mom.

25:58.349 --> 26:00.367
You were with her the entire morning.

26:00.401 --> 26:01.485
I swear.

26:01.519 --> 26:03.386
And you can call her manager.

26:03.421 --> 26:05.522
The box cutter is for her job.

26:05.556 --> 26:08.658
All right. I'll reverse the expulsion.

26:08.692 --> 26:10.327
Yes!

26:10.361 --> 26:12.579
But you still have Saturday
detention for a month.

26:12.630 --> 26:13.663
- What?
- Why?

26:13.697 --> 26:17.250
We have a strict no-weapon policy.

26:17.301 --> 26:18.368
You know that.

26:18.402 --> 26:19.669
But whatever the reason,

26:19.704 --> 26:21.571
you can't have a knife in your possession.

26:21.606 --> 26:23.473
- End of story.
- All right.

26:23.508 --> 26:25.675
What about field hockey?

26:25.710 --> 26:28.345
She can still play field hockey.

26:29.564 --> 26:32.449
So you're punishing me for having a job?

26:32.483 --> 26:34.568
No, I'm punishing you
for breaking the rules.

26:34.602 --> 26:37.687
- Is is some bull...
- Don't you even think about finishing that sentence.

26:37.722 --> 26:39.556
If it were her, you would have
kissed her ass for making a mistake.

26:39.590 --> 26:40.690
But with me,

26:40.725 --> 26:42.492
you want to punish me anyway?

26:42.527 --> 26:43.593
And for what?

26:43.628 --> 26:46.496
For looking how I look?

26:46.531 --> 26:48.465
Is this how you run this school?

26:48.499 --> 26:50.267
Don't you go there with me, Sharee.

26:50.301 --> 26:51.668
I am doing my job,

26:51.702 --> 26:55.338
and I treat all my students the same.

27:01.679 --> 27:04.181
Sharee, that's a win.

27:04.215 --> 27:05.298
You still get to play field hockey.

27:05.349 --> 27:07.250
You are so dumb. You know that?

27:07.268 --> 27:08.552
I went to bat for you.

27:08.586 --> 27:10.270
I'm the one who got you out of this.

27:10.304 --> 27:11.638
Oh, please! You don't give a damn about me.

27:11.689 --> 27:13.607
The only reason why you did any of that

27:13.641 --> 27:16.259
was so I could help you win the
game and make your daddy happy.

27:16.277 --> 27:18.361
- That is not true.
- The game, the game.

27:18.396 --> 27:20.447
- The game.
- Hey!

27:20.481 --> 27:22.365
- Hey!
- Yo, get off of me.

27:22.400 --> 27:24.484
What are you doing? I'm
just trying to talk to you.

27:24.535 --> 27:26.436
Don't you touch me, all right?

27:26.454 --> 27:27.621
- Get off of me!
- Break it up!

27:27.655 --> 27:29.272
Break it up.

27:35.379 --> 27:38.298
You know, I don't think I ever realized

27:38.332 --> 27:40.500
the connection between
your work in the '80s

27:40.551 --> 27:42.252
and your work now.

27:42.286 --> 27:43.486
How the body is this organic thing

27:43.521 --> 27:45.689
and yet we've moved
into this digital space.

27:45.723 --> 27:49.259
Are you aware you say every
statement like a question?

27:49.293 --> 27:50.694
I do?

27:50.728 --> 27:53.296
I do.

27:53.314 --> 27:55.465
Hey. Hey, you see these
face prints over there?

27:55.483 --> 27:57.634
They totally remind me
of these potato prints

27:57.702 --> 27:59.402
I used to do in kindergarten,

27:59.437 --> 28:01.204
except these cost like five grand each.

28:01.239 --> 28:04.307
What do all these little red dots mean?

28:08.246 --> 28:10.313
It means the piece has been sold.

28:10.348 --> 28:13.283
Oh. Oh, wow. She doesn't have any.

28:13.317 --> 28:16.586
Oh, I just stepped on a rake, didn't I?

28:21.208 --> 28:22.359
Yeah.

28:27.498 --> 28:29.466
Hey!

28:29.500 --> 28:32.435
You still want that
letter of recommendation?

28:34.372 --> 28:36.273
Whatever.

28:36.307 --> 28:37.474
They're right.

28:37.508 --> 28:39.509
My new work sucks.

28:39.543 --> 28:42.479
I don't even know what I'm doing anymore.

28:42.568 --> 28:44.336
One minute they're holding you up

28:44.370 --> 28:46.271
like you're some sort of a goddess.

28:46.305 --> 28:49.441
The next, they don't even know
how to spell your name right.

28:51.477 --> 28:53.378
I like your stuff.

28:53.412 --> 28:56.581
You like it 'cause you want something.

28:56.616 --> 29:00.218
I remember what that looks like.

29:00.253 --> 29:02.187
You want to be happy?

29:02.221 --> 29:04.556
Don't go to art school.

29:13.626 --> 29:15.327
Hey, guys.

29:15.345 --> 29:16.595
Congratulations.

29:16.629 --> 29:19.698
Our first official game became
our first official forfeit.

29:19.732 --> 29:21.800
We're setting records already.

29:21.835 --> 29:23.502
Why did you cancel the game?

29:23.520 --> 29:24.703
Oh, let's see.

29:24.737 --> 29:26.638
Well, first, Bay quit.

29:26.673 --> 29:28.740
Then my two star players
decided they'd rather

29:28.775 --> 29:30.609
beat each other up than the opposing team.

29:30.643 --> 29:31.710
That's not what happened.

29:31.744 --> 29:33.779
Yeah, she didn't even get a punch in.

29:33.813 --> 29:36.348
Thanks, guys.

29:36.382 --> 29:37.716
So proud to be your coach.

29:56.402 --> 29:58.737
I'm sorry I got you
involved in all of this.

29:58.771 --> 30:02.374
No, I'm sorry I screwed up
your letter of recommendation.

30:05.378 --> 30:07.613
I don't think that really matters anymore.

30:15.655 --> 30:17.356
Hey.

30:17.390 --> 30:19.358
Hey.

30:19.392 --> 30:22.411
I'm sorry that your game got canceled.

30:22.445 --> 30:24.446
Forfeited, actually.

30:25.615 --> 30:27.499
Pretty sure this isn't going to help,

30:27.534 --> 30:28.800
but I bought you something today.

30:28.835 --> 30:30.419
For your new place.

30:31.788 --> 30:34.506
What's that?

30:34.541 --> 30:35.680
Door-stopper?

30:35.713 --> 30:37.598
They're pot holders. Oh, my God!

30:37.632 --> 30:39.333
You're never going to survive on your own.

30:39.367 --> 30:42.436
I'm kidding. I know what it is.

30:42.470 --> 30:43.804
Just promise me you're not
going to be the kind of guy

30:43.838 --> 30:45.806
who uses his socks to get
things out of the oven.

30:45.840 --> 30:47.474
You'll burn yourself,

30:47.509 --> 30:48.575
and it's gross.

30:48.610 --> 30:51.678
Okay as long as you show
me how to work an oven.

30:53.348 --> 30:55.549
Gotcha. I'm still joking.

30:57.352 --> 30:59.319
You know...

31:00.788 --> 31:03.724
you can always come home if you need to.

31:05.627 --> 31:07.628
And I hope you'll want to.

31:09.364 --> 31:11.498
Of course.

31:11.533 --> 31:13.534
Where else am I going
to get butterscotch bars?

31:32.770 --> 31:34.555
Hey.

31:34.589 --> 31:35.756
What brings you here?

31:35.790 --> 31:39.426
Why didn't you become an artist?

31:39.460 --> 31:42.329
I wasn't aware I didn't.

31:42.363 --> 31:45.532
You know what I mean. A professional one.

31:45.567 --> 31:48.452
Maybe I didn't want it enough.

31:48.486 --> 31:50.404
Maybe I didn't think I was good enough.

31:50.438 --> 31:52.406
Maybe it just looked too hard.

31:52.440 --> 31:55.509
And sad.

31:55.543 --> 31:57.411
Is it sad?

31:57.445 --> 32:01.515
I'm starting to wonder if I
really want to go to art school.

32:01.549 --> 32:03.617
Going to school is one thing.

32:03.651 --> 32:06.353
Being an artist is another.

32:06.387 --> 32:10.457
I think it's a whole series of choices.

32:10.491 --> 32:13.460
You know? It doesn't come
down to just one opportunity

32:13.494 --> 32:16.730
or one person's opinion.

32:16.764 --> 32:18.365
At least I hope it doesn't.

32:20.635 --> 32:22.603
How was your day?

32:22.637 --> 32:24.504
Oh... you know.

32:24.539 --> 32:26.306
The usual.

32:26.341 --> 32:28.742
Flew to Denver and back on a private jet.

32:28.776 --> 32:31.511
Lost my only client
somewhere along the way.

32:31.546 --> 32:33.447
The first half sounds fun.

32:33.481 --> 32:34.648
It wasn't.

32:34.682 --> 32:36.383
The guy was a total jerk.

32:36.417 --> 32:39.353
But it hasn't stopped
me from kicking myself

32:39.387 --> 32:41.521
all night for letting it go.

32:41.556 --> 32:43.357
Well, you don't want to
work for some jerk anyway.

32:43.391 --> 32:44.558
I don't.

32:44.592 --> 32:47.494
But I do need to work for somebody.

32:49.397 --> 32:50.797
You know what I've decided...

32:50.832 --> 32:53.433
I'm not letting unhappy people

32:53.468 --> 32:54.601
decide what I get to do.

32:54.636 --> 32:57.437
That sounds like a good policy.

33:13.738 --> 33:15.455
Is Toby here?

33:15.490 --> 33:17.624
He's probably in his room.

33:17.659 --> 33:19.293
Ahem.

33:19.327 --> 33:22.396
I guess you've heard we had to forfeit.

33:22.430 --> 33:25.465
Uh, yeah. I made it as
far as the parking lot

33:25.500 --> 33:28.435
and then I saw the Hoffman
team getting on the bus,

33:28.469 --> 33:30.604
and...

33:30.638 --> 33:32.389
I'm so sorry.

33:32.423 --> 33:33.707
They seemed quite happy

33:33.741 --> 33:35.509
that they didn't have to go ten rounds

33:35.543 --> 33:38.345
with the Carlton bruisers.

33:38.379 --> 33:40.714
Okay, look...

33:42.767 --> 33:45.385
I know what you're going to say.

33:45.420 --> 33:46.620
That the school's too rough.

33:46.654 --> 33:48.655
And that you want to take me out of it.

33:48.690 --> 33:50.390
But I can explain...

33:54.629 --> 33:58.265
I'm actually starting
to think that that school

33:58.299 --> 34:00.300
is perfect for you.

34:00.335 --> 34:02.536
You get to fight.

34:02.570 --> 34:04.538
You get to blackmail senators.

34:04.572 --> 34:07.274
How long before you start robbing banks?

34:08.643 --> 34:09.743
You know what...

34:09.777 --> 34:12.512
I'm really sorry about what
happened over the summer.

34:12.547 --> 34:16.516
But I've done everything
I can to make up for it.

34:16.551 --> 34:18.284
And the only reason I got in a fight

34:18.319 --> 34:19.418
in the first place

34:19.454 --> 34:21.655
was because I was totally obsessed

34:21.688 --> 34:23.556
with trying to make this team work.

34:23.591 --> 34:25.592
And I probably lost a friend over it.

34:25.626 --> 34:26.592
And why?

34:26.627 --> 34:28.594
So that you would go to a game,

34:28.629 --> 34:30.630
and for the first time in a month,

34:30.665 --> 34:33.734
look at me like I wasn't
a total disappointment.

34:33.768 --> 34:37.670
Yeah, this whole dumb field
hockey experiment was for you.

34:37.705 --> 34:40.407
But you're never going to let it go.

34:40.440 --> 34:42.775
So just do whatever you want.

34:42.810 --> 34:44.710
Throw us out of the house.

34:44.746 --> 34:46.746
Pretend like you never
found out about the switch.

34:46.781 --> 34:49.449
I don't even care anymore.

